lines.text: Nina, could you possibly run Ellen into town?
No. But I can run her over.
You're manipulative, stubborn and selfish!
Not all at once.
[Luke and Woody get in Maggie's way as she is about to give a defibrillating shock to a patient]
Come on! Move or die!
What are you doing? Where the hell are you going?
Tina.
Did you forget to say goodbye or something?
Tina.
I can't believe you were going to go without even saying anything. To Australia without even saying goodbye. What where you thinking? Did you think I wouldn't notice? You lied. How could you just go?
Listen, it's not like that. You don't understand, and I can't explain.
You owe it to me to try.
I need to take ten steps back. I don't want to look back on my life thinking I could have done more.
Yeah, but you don't have to run away half way across the world.
It's just something I have to do.
Get off the train, Sean, just please get off the train.
I can't.
For me, for you. I just know you want to, now, Sean just please get off the train!
Why now?

[shouts]
Get off the train?
Stop saying that!
I'll walk away any second!
Well, then go!

[pause]
I can't go.
Now leave me alone or I'll call Security.
I *am* Security.
Then kindly throw yourself out.
[Selena throws Bex against a wall after Bex, unknowingly, slept with Selina's husband]
You and me... we've got business.
Look I told you - I had no idea! I am sorry, it's not going to happen again!

I don't care about what you do with him. You can keep him. All I care about is me. Now I've just started here and I am not about to be made a laughing stock by some stupid little slapper like you! Do you understand me?
Yes.
You mention one word of you and him to anyone - and your life will not be worth living! Do you understand me again? Rebecca?
Yes.
[Selena walks off]
Harry, have you got a minute? I could do with a second opinion on these results.

[patronisingly]
My pleasure. I'm always happy to offer my expert advice.
Er, just your opinion. I've got the expert bit covered, thank you.
Get on the train.
It's so unfair.
This may be our last chance. Come on, get on.
Marry me.
What?
You heard, marry me.
Shut up and get on the train.
Well?
Look, get on the train.
Just say you'll marry me.
Tina, I'm going to London, in two days I fly to Australia, I fly in two days, two days!
Huh?
You know you're making this so much harder?
You're leaving me. I'm hardly going to make it easy for you.
You're the only thing I'll miss.
Is that a yes?
I love you. With all my feet.
Why does it feel like I'm having an affair with my own girlfriend?
Don't knock it, some might say you've got the best of both worlds.
[a flat screen for tracking patients' waiting times has just been delivered to the department]
What on earth is that for?
Action replays of your greatest life-saving moments. I love short films.
I see your humour implant didn't take, then.

[Chloe has just bought a houseboat]
So this boat, what's it called?
Not it - she! It's called Kestrel... ain't that lovely?
What part of "one last chance" do you not understand?
I was talking to my colleague!
Well she must have trouble hearing 'cos the last thing I heard you were talking to her through her mouth in the staff room!
I could kill Ellen for taking out a loan with a psychopath...
It wouldn't be worth it - unless we could sell her body for scrap!

[referring to a woman who has been bothering the men in the department all day]
She's probably just lonely.
Or she needs her chimney swept

[referring to Nathan]
I bet he's a John Major.
What do you mean?
He tucks his shirt into his pants!
Charlie, you know that motel by the bypass?
Yes
Well the managers a friend of mine...
And?
Well, I thought it might be good for a room...

[pulling a face]
Ooooooh!
Not for us! For the Devern family!
Shame, I thought my luck had changed there...
Nathan just made an interesting point.
There's a first time for everything.
There's no I in team.
No, but there's a me if you look close enough.

[to Maggie]
You will never guess what just happened.
Yeah well so long as I don't get the blame I don't care.
Nathan just asked my out.
Nathan as in Spencer?
[Selena nods]
Well I hope you told him to get stuffed.
[Selena looks away]
You didn't did you?
Look, I didn't say yes. Look, he's not that bad, he's good looking, he's successful.
Yeah and what happened to I need a good man? He's obviously a snake, what is it with you and dodgy blokes? Please, Selena, just wait for a decent man.
You might be right. Do you know what though? Do you know what was lovely? Just having someone actually ask me out, even if it was Nathan.
Nathan asked you out. Isn't he gay?
[walks away with a huge grin on her face]
